                      ATTRIBUTE_ROW_ENTRIES = [

                          :attribute_type,

                      def initialize

                        super(&method(:format_row))

                      def format_row(row)
          
      190. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    190. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :attribute_type) { |s| AttributeType.new(s) }
          
      191. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    191. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :desc) { row.delete(:description) }
          
      192. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    192. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :restricted, &COLUMN_AS_BOOLEAN)
          
      193. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    193. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :read_only, &COLUMN_AS_BOOLEAN)
          
      194. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    194. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :options) { |s| {"type" => "Array", "value" => s.split(',').map(&:strip)} }
          
      195. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    195. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :match) { |s| {"type" => "Regexp", "value" => Regexp.new(s).source} }
          
      196. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    196. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :validation) { row[:options] || row[:match] }
          
      197. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    197. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :hidden, &COLUMN_AS_BOOLEAN)
          
      198. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    198. 
            
            

            

                        replace_row_column(row, :unique, &COLUMN_AS_BOOLEAN)
          
      199. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    199. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      200. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    200. 
            
            

            

            
          
      201.

                      def prepare_changeset(filename: nil, input_io: nil, &validation_err_block)
          
      211. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    211. 
            
            

            

                        ModelsChangeset.new.tap do |changeset|
          
      212. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    212. 
            
            

            

                          context = {}
          
      213. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    213. 
            
            

            

                          each_csv_row(filename: filename, input_io: input_io) do |row, lineno|
          
      214. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    214. 
            
            

            

                            p = NestedRowProcessor.new(row, lineno, context)
          
      215. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    215. 
            
            

            

                            process_row(p, changeset)
          
      216. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    216. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      217. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    217. 
            
            

            

            
          
      218. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    218. 
            
            

            

                          # After configuring attributes, set defaults for certain attribute properties.
          
      219. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    219. 
            
            

            

                          changeset.models.all.each do |model|
          
      220. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    220. 
            
            

            

                            model.template.attributes.all.each do |attribute|
          
      221. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    221. 
            
            

            

                              attribute.set_field_defaults!
          
      222. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    222. 
            
            

            

                            end
          
      223. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    223. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      224. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    224. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      225. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    225. 
            
            

            

                      rescue ImportError => e
          
      226. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    226. 
            
            

            

                        validation_err_block.call(e.message)
          
      227. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    227. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      228.

                      def process_model_config(models, row_processor)

                          models.build_model(model_name).build_template.tap { |t| t.name = model_name }

                        end
          
      236.

                        row_processor.process(:identifier, :model_name) do |identifier, template|

                          template.identifier = identifier

                      def process_parent_config(models, row_processor)
          
      242. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    242. 
            
            

            

                        row_processor.process(:parent_model_name, :model_name) do |parent_model_name, template|
          
      243. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    243. 
            
            

            

                          if template.parent && !template.parent.empty? && template.parent != parent_model_name
          
      244. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    244. 
            
            

            

                            raise ImportError.new("Model #{template.name} was provided multiple parent_model_names: #{template.parent} and #{parent_model_name}")
          
      245. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    245. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      246. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    246. 
            
            

            

            
          
      247. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    247. 
            
            

            

                          template.parent = parent_model_name
          
      248. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    248. 
            
            

            

            
          
      249. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    249. 
            
            

            

                          template.build_attributes.build_attribute(template.parent).tap do |parent_att|
          
      250. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    250. 
            
            

            

                            parent_att.name = parent_att.attribute_name = parent_model_name
          
      251. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    251. 
            
            

            

                            parent_att.attribute_type = Etna::Clients::Magma::AttributeType::PARENT
          
      252. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    252. 
            
            

            

                            parent_att.link_model_name = parent_model_name
          
      253. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    253. 
            
            

            

                            parent_att.desc = prettify(parent_model_name)
          
      254. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    254. 
            
            

            

                            parent_att.display_name = prettify(parent_model_name)
          
      255. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    255. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      256. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    256. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      257. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    257. 
            
            

            

            
          
      258. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    258. 
            
            

            

                        row_processor.process(:parent_link_type, :model_name, :parent_model_name) do |parent_link_type, template|
          
      259. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    259. 
            
            

            

                          reciprocal = models.find_reciprocal(model_name: template.name, link_attribute_name: template.parent)
          
      260. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    260. 
            
            

            

                          if reciprocal && reciprocal.attribute_type.to_s != parent_link_type
          
      261. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    261. 
            
            

            

                            raise ImportError.new("Model #{template.name} was provided multiple parent_link_types: #{reciprocal.attribute_type} and #{parent_link_type}")
          
      262. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    262. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      263. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    263. 
            
            

            

            
          
      264. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    264. 
            
            

            

                          if reciprocal && reciprocal.attribute_name != template.name
          
      265. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    265. 
            
            

            

                            raise ImportError.new("Model #{template.name} is linked to #{template.parent}, but the reciprocal link is misnamed as '#{reciprocal.attribute_name}'.")
          
      266. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    266. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      267. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    267. 
            
            

            

            
          
      268. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    268. 
            
            

            

                          models.build_model(template.parent).tap do |parent_model|
          
      269. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    269. 
            
            

            

                            parent_model_attribute_by_model_name = parent_model.build_template.build_attributes.attribute(template.name)
          
      270. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    270. 
            
            

            

                            if parent_model_attribute_by_model_name && !reciprocal
          
      271. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    271. 
            
            

            

                              raise ImportError.new("Model #{template.parent} is linked as a parent to #{template.name}, but it already has an attribute named #{template.name} #{parent_model_attribute_by_model_name.raw}.")
          
      272. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    272. 
            
            

            

                            end
          
      273. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    273. 
            
            

            

            
          
      274. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    274. 
            
            

            

                            parent_model.build_template.build_attributes.build_attribute(template.name).tap do |attr|
          
      275. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    275. 
            
            

            

                              attr.attribute_name = attr.name = template.name
          
      276. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    276. 
            
            

            

                              attr.attribute_type = parent_link_type
          
      277. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    277. 
            
            

            

                              attr.link_model_name = template.name
          
      278. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    278. 
            
            

            

                              attr.desc = prettify(template.name)
          
      279. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    279. 
            
            

            

                              attr.display_name = prettify(template.name)
          
      280. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    280. 
            
            

            

                            end
          
      281. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    281. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      282. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    282. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      283. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    283. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      284. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    284. 
            
            

            

            
          
      285.

                      def process_matrix_constants(changeset, row_processor)
          
      286. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    286. 
            
            

            

                        row_processor.process(:matrix_constant) do |matrix_constant|
          
      287. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    287. 
            
            

            

                          # Lines that start with the sentinel are a distinct 'group'
          
      288. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    288. 
            
            

            

                          if matrix_constant.start_with?(COPY_OPTIONS_SENTINEL)
          
      289. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    289. 
            
            

            

                            matrix_constant = matrix_constant.slice((COPY_OPTIONS_SENTINEL.length)..-1)
          
      290. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    290. 
            
            

            

                            changeset.matrix_constants[matrix_constant] = []
          
      291. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    291. 
            
            

            

                          else
          
      292. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    292. 
            
            

            

                            # Until the sentinel is seen again, all further entries belong to the set.
          
      293. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    293. 
            
            

            

                            changeset.matrix_constants[changeset.matrix_constants.keys.last] << matrix_constant
          
      294. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    294. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      295. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    295. 
            
            

            

            
          
      296. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    296. 
            
            

            

                          matrix_constant
          
      297. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    297. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      298. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    298. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      299. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    299. 
            
            

            

            
          
      300. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    300. 
            1
            

            

                      def process_attribute_properties(changeset, row_processor)
          
      301. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    301. 
            
            

            

                        models = changeset.models
          
      302. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    302. 
            
            

            

            
          
      303. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    303. 
            
            

            

                        row_processor.process(:attribute_name, :model_name) do |attribute_name, template|
          
      304. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    304. 
            
            

            

                          attributes = template.build_attributes
          
      305. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    305. 
            
            

            

            
          
      306. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    306. 
            
            

            

                          existing_attribute = attributes.attribute(attribute_name)
          
      307. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    307. 
            
            

            

                          if existing_attribute
          
      308. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    308. 
            
            

            

                            if existing_attribute.attribute_type != Etna::Clients::Magma::AttributeType::COLLECTION
          
      309. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    309. 
            
            

            

                              raise ImportError.new("Attribute #{attribute_name} of model #{template.name} has duplicate definitions!")
          
      310. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    310. 
            
            

            

                            end
          
      311. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    311. 
            
            

            

            
          
      312. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    312. 
            
            

            

                            # Clear its definition; implicit attributes are overwritten by explicit definitions if they exist.
          
      313. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    313. 
            
            

            

                            attributes.raw.delete(attribute_name)
          
      314. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    314. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      315. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    315. 
            
            

            

            
          
      316. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    316. 
            
            

            

                          attributes.build_attribute(attribute_name).tap { |att| att.name = att.attribute_name = attribute_name }
          
      317. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    317. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      318. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    318. 
            
            

            

            
          
      319. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    319. 
            
            

            

                        row_processor.process(:new_attribute_name, :attribute_name, :model_name) do |new_attribute_name, att, template|
          
      320. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    320. 
            
            

            

                          renames = changeset.build_renames(template.name)
          
      321. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    321. 
            
            

            

                          if renames.include?(att.name) && renames[att.name] != new_attribute_name
          
      322. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    322. 
            
            

            

                            raise ImportError.new("Found multiple new_attribute_name values for #{template.name}'s #{att.name}': #{new_attribute_name} or #{renames[att.name]}?")
          
      323. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    323. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      324. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    324. 
            
            

            

            
          
      325. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    325. 
            
            

            

                          renames[att.attribute_name] = new_attribute_name
          
      326. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    326. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      327. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    327. 
            
            

            

            
          
      328. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    328. 
            
            

            

                        ATTRIBUTE_ROW_ENTRIES.each do |prop_name|
          
      329. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    329. 
            
            

            

                          row_processor.process(prop_name, :model_name, :attribute_name) do |value, template, att|
          
      330. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    330. 
            
            

            

                            if att.raw.include?(prop_name.to_s)
          
      331. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    331. 
            
            

            

                              raise ImportError.new("Value for #{prop_name} on attribute #{att.attribute_name} has duplicate definitions!")
          
      332. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    332. 
            
            

            

                            end
          
      333. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    333. 
            
            

            

            
          
      334. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    334. 
            
            

            

                            att.send(:"#{prop_name}=", value)
          
      335. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    335. 
            
            

            

            
          
      336. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    336. 
            
            

            

                            if att.attribute_type && att.link_model_name
          
      337. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    337. 
            
            

            

                              if att.attribute_type == Etna::Clients::Magma::AttributeType::LINK && models.find_reciprocal(model_name: template.name, attribute: att).nil?
          
      338. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    338. 
            
            

            

                                models.build_model(att.link_model_name).build_template.build_attributes.build_attribute(template.name).tap do |rec_att|
          
      339. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    339. 
            
            

            

                                  rec_att.attribute_name = rec_att.name = template.name
          
      340.

                    def ensure_model_tree(model_name, seen = Set.new)
          
      122.

                      attributes = source_model.template.attributes

                    def ensure_model_link(model_name, link_model_name, attribute_name)
          
      148. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    148. 
            
            

            

                      return unless (model = source_models.model(model_name))

                      return unless (source_attribute = model.template.attributes.attribute(attribute_name))

      151.

                      return unless (link_model = source_models.model(link_model_name))

                      link_model_attributes = link_model.template.attributes
          
      153.

                      reciprocal = link_model_attributes.all.find do |attr|
          
      154. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    154. 
            
            

            

                        attr.link_model_name == model_name
          
      155. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    155. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      156. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    156. 
            
            

            

            
          
      157.

                      target_model_name = target_of_source(model_name)
          
      158.

                      target_link_model_name = target_of_source(link_model_name)
          
      159. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    159. 
            
            

            

            
          
      160. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    160. 
            
            

            

                      target_attributes = target_models.model(target_model_name).template.attributes
          
      161.

                      return if target_attributes.attribute_keys.include?(target_link_model_name)
          
      162. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    162. 
            
            

            

            
          
      163. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    163. 
            
            

            

                      add_link = AddLinkAction.new
          
      164. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    164. 
            
            

            

                      add_link.links << AddLinkDefinition.new(model_name: target_model_name, attribute_name: target_link_model_name, type: source_attribute.attribute_type)
          
      165. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    165. 
            
            

            

                      add_link.links << AddLinkDefinition.new(model_name: target_link_model_name, attribute_name: reciprocal.attribute_name, type: reciprocal.attribute_type)
          
      166. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    166.

                    def ensure_model_attribute(model_name, attribute_name)
          
      171.

                      return unless (model = source_models.model(model_name))
          
      172.

                      return unless (source_attribute = model.template.attributes.attribute(attribute_name))
          
      173. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    173. 
            
            

            

            
          
      174. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    174. 
            
            

            

                      target_model_name = target_of_source(model_name)
          
      175. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    175. 
            
            

            

                      target_attribute, target_attribute_name = ensure_model_attribute_target_rename(model_name, attribute_name)
          
      176. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    176. 
            
            

            

            
          
      177. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    177. 
            
            

            

                      if target_attribute.nil?
          
      178. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    178. 
            
            

            

                        add_attribute = AddAttributeAction.new(
          
      179. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    179. 
            
            

            

                            model_name: target_model_name,
          
      180.

                            attribute_name: target_attribute_name,
          
      181.

                        )
          
      182. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    182. 
            
            

            

            
          
      183. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    183. 
            
            

            

                        Attribute.copy(source_attribute, add_attribute)
          
      184.

                        queue_update(add_attribute)
          
      185. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    185. 
            
            

            

                      else
          
      186. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    186. 
            
            

            

                        # If there are is no diff, don't produce an action.
          
      187. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    187. 
            
            

            

                        target_attribute = Attribute.new(target_attribute.raw)
          
      188. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    188. 
            
            

            

                        target_attribute.set_field_defaults!
          
      189. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    189. 
            
            

            

            
          
      190. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    190. 
            
            

            

                        source_attribute = Attribute.new(source_attribute.raw)
          
      191. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    191. 
            
            

            

                        source_attribute.set_field_defaults!
          
      192.

                        source_editable = source_attribute.raw.slice(*Attribute::EDITABLE_ATTRIBUTE_ATTRIBUTES.map(&:to_s))
          
      194.

                        target_editable = target_attribute.raw.slice(*Attribute::EDITABLE_ATTRIBUTE_ATTRIBUTES.map(&:to_s))
          
      195. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    195. 
            
            

            

            
          
      196.

                        if source_editable == target_editable
          
      197.

      199. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    199. 
            
            

            

            
          
      200. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    200. 
            
            

            

                        update_attribute = UpdateAttributeAction.new(
          
      201.

                            model_name: target_model_name,

                            attribute_name: target_attribute_name,

                        Attribute.copy(source_attribute, update_attribute, attributes: Attribute::EDITABLE_ATTRIBUTE_ATTRIBUTES)

                        queue_update(update_attribute)
          
      207.

                      end
          
      208. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    208. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      209. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    209. 
            
            

            

            
          
      210. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    210. 
            
            

            

                    # Returns a tuple of the target's attribute, post rename if necessary, if it exists, and the name of the target attribute
          
      211. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    211. 
            
            

            

                    # cases here:
          
      212. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    212. 
            
            

            

                    # 1.  There is no rename for the attribute
          
      213. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    213. 
            
            

            

                    #  a. There target attribute already exists -> [target_attribute, attribute_name]
          
      214. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    214. 
            
            

            

                    #  b. The target attribute does not exist -> [nil, attribute_name]
          
      215. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    215. 
            
            

            

                    # 2.  There is an expected rename from the source
          
      216. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    216. 
            
            

            

                    #  a. The target has neither the renamed attribute or the original attribute -> [nil, new_attribute_name]
          
      217. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    217. 
            
            

            

                    #  b. The target has the renamed attribute already -> [renamed_attribute, new_attribute_name]
          
      218. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    218. 
            
            

            

                    #  c. The target has the source attribute, which is not yet renamed. -> [renamed_attribute, new_attribute_name]
          
      219. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    219. 
            1
            

            

                    def ensure_model_attribute_target_rename(model_name, attribute_name)
          
      220. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    220. 
            
            

            

                      target_model_name = target_of_source(model_name)
          
      221. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    221. 
            
            

            

                      target_attribute_name = target_attribute_of_source(model_name, attribute_name)
          
      222. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    222. 
            
            

            

                      return nil unless (target_model = target_models.model(target_model_name))
          
      223. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    223. 
            
            

            

            
          
      224. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    224. 
            
            

            

                      target_original_attribute = target_model.template.attributes.attribute(target_attribute_name)
          
      225. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    225. 
            
            

            

            
          
      226. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    226. 
            
            

            

                      if renames && (attribute_renames = renames[model_name]) && (new_name = attribute_renames[attribute_name])
          
      227. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    227. 
            
            

            

                        new_name = target_attribute_of_source(model_name, new_name)
          
      228. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    228. 
            
            

            

            
          
      229. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    229. 
            
            

            

                        unless target_model.template.attributes.include?(new_name)
          
      230. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    230. 
            
            

            

                          if target_original_attribute
          
      231. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    231. 
            
            

            

                            rename = RenameAttributeAction.new(model_name: target_model_name, attribute_name: target_attribute_name, new_attribute_name: new_name)
          
      232. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    232. 
            
            

            

                            queue_update(rename)
          
      233. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    233. 
            
            

            

                          else
          
      234. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    234. 
            
            

            

                            return [nil, new_name]
          
      235. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    235. 
            
            

            

                          end
          
      236. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    236. 
            
            

            

                        end
          
      237. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    237. 
            
            

            

            
          
      238. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    238. 
            
            

            

                        return [target_model.template.attributes.attribute(new_name), new_name]
          
      239. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    239. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      240. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    240. 
            
            

            

            
          
      241. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    241. 
            
            

            

                      [target_original_attribute, target_attribute_name]
          
      242. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    242. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      243. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    243. 
            
            

            

            
          
      244. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    244. 
            
            

            

                    # Non cyclical, non re-entrant due to the requirement that parents cannot form a cycle.
          
      245. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    245. 
            
            

            

                    # This method, and it's partner prepare_parent, should never call into any re-entrant or potentially
          
      246. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    246. 
            
            

            

                    # cyclical method, like ensure_model_tree.
          
      247. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    247. 
            1
            

            

                    def ensure_model(model_name)
          
      248. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    248. 
            
            

            

                      return unless (source_model = source_models.model(model_name))
          
      249. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    249. 
            
            

            

                      target_model_name = target_of_source(model_name)
          
      250. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    250. 
            
            

            

                      return if target_models.model_keys.include?(target_model_name)
          
      251. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    251. 
            
            

            

            
          
      252. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    252. 
            
            

            

                      template = source_model.template
          
      253. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    253. 
            
            

            

            
          
      254. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    254. 
            
            

            

                      add_model_action = AddModelAction.new(
          
      255. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    255. 
            
            

            

                          {
          
      256. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    256. 
            
            

            

                              model_name: target_model_name,
          
      257. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    257. 
            
            

            

                              identifier: template.identifier,
          
      258. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    258. 
            
            

            

                          }
          
      259. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    259. 
            
            

            

                      )
          
      260. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    260. 
            
            

            

            
          
      261. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    261. 
            
            

            

                      parents = template.attributes.all.select { |a| a.attribute_type == AttributeType::PARENT }
          
      262. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    262. 
            
            

            

                      parent_model_name, parent_link_type = prepare_parent(model_name, template, parents)
          
      263. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    263. 
            
            

            

                      unless parent_model_name.nil?
          
      264. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    264. 
            
            

            

                        add_model_action.parent_model_name = parent_model_name
          
      265. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    265. 
            
            

            

                        add_model_action.parent_link_type = parent_link_type
          
      266. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    266. 
            
            

            

                      end
          
      267. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    267. 
            
            

            

            
          
      268. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    268. 
            
            

            

                      queue_update(add_model_action)
          
      269. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    269. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      270. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    270. 
            
            

            

            
          
      271. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    271. 
            
            

            

                    # Non cyclical, non re-entrant due to the requirement that parents cannot form a cycle.
          
      272. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    272. 
            
            

            

                    # This method, and it's partner and ensure_model, should never call into any re-entrant or potentially
          
      273. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    273. 
            
            

            

                    # cyclical method, like ensure_model_tree.
          
      274.

                    def prepare_parent(model_name, template, parents)
          
      275.

                      return [nil, nil] if parents.empty?
          
      276. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    276. 
            
            

            

                      return [nil, nil] unless (parent_model = source_models.model(template.parent))
          
      277. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    277. 
            
            

            

                      return [nil, nil] unless (child_attribute = parent_model.template.attributes.attribute(model_name))
          
      278. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    278. 
            
            

            

            
          
      279. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    279. 
            
            

            

                      ensure_model(template.parent)
          
      280. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    280. 
            
            

            

            
          
      281. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    281. 
            
            

            

                      [
          
      282. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    282. 
            
            

            

                          target_of_source(template.parent),
          
      283. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    283. 
            
            

            

                          child_attribute.attribute_type
          
      284. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    284. 
            
            

            

                      ]
          
      285. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    285. 
            
            

            

                    end
          
      286. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    286. 
            
            

            

            
          
      287. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    287. 
            1
            

            

                    def self.models_affected_by(action)
          
      288. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    288. 
            
            

            

                      case action
          
      289. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    289. 
            
            

            

                      when Etna::Clients::Magma::RenameAttributeAction
          
      290. 
        
      
      
        
      
          
    290. 
            
            

            

                        [action.model_name]
